    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "There's some misunderstanding. `prank` and `broadcast` [only change the `msg.sender` of **the following external call** ](https://book.getfoundry.sh/cheatcodes/prank)by design. They do not change the current `msg.sender` of the script execution.\r\n\r\n> It does work correctly when passing in the private key via --private-key 0xabc.\r\n\r\nIt behaves the same. The difference is: when you pass a `--private-key` he sets that key as the default `msg.sender`, the one that calls the script contract `run()`. You can also call it with `--sender`. If you don't set either one, then foundry will call the script contract with a default one (0x1804c8AB1F12E6bbf3894d4083f33e07309d1f38)\r\n",
